name: none
description: Those without weapons are the economic backbone of Elf society

description: Dark bows draw no attention, allowing their user to slither in the night

description: Draconic markings bode ill for those standing in its way

description: Markings of tradition adorn this ceremonial bow

description: Draconic lances wielded by tribes of elves as fierce and wild as their prey

description: Lances dripping with gold leaf lull opponents into a false sense of security

description: Elves possess unparalleled quartz craftsmanship, through which they imbue their weapons with eternal sharpness

name: Staff_golden
description: A gold-plated staff passed down through generations now serves as a symbol of diplomacy

name: Staff_jade
description: Only the finest tribes of artisans ever possessed the ability to craft such opulent weapons

name: body_blue
description: Elves whose kin have been exposed to the deep blue waters of the Sea of Liquidity bear a blue tinge

name: body_green
description: The skin of Elfis whose generations have spent their time among the trees of the Forests of Yield has become green

name: body_pale
description: The icy peaks of the Bearish Mountains are said to be home to Elfis whose skin is paler than snow

name: body_pink
description: Exposure to the red arid soil of the Bullish Valleys has made the skin of each new generation become slightly more pink

name: body_red
description: Red Elves are believed to be descendants of the Ancestral Degens, whose skin was tempered by the fiery forges of the Degen Inferno

name: body_yellow
description: Yellow elves are believed to be descendants of the Ancient Proposers, whose rules of governance still guide to this day

name: none
description: Some elves shun the moral rigitude of society in favor of being one with nature

name: Breastplate_blue
description: Full-body armor made of magical quartz. Movement is somewhat restricted, but it’s highly protective against Degen magics

name: Breastplate_Draconic
description: Full-body armor made with the scales of ancient dragons. Although said to still roam the land, nobody has seen them since the fall of Mount Qogs

name: Breastplate_golden
description: Full-body armor made of gold and worn by elite warriors. The magical quartz infused in it makes it lighter than fabric

name: clothes_colonist_blue
description: Light clothing, good for fast travel. Its blue color is obtained from Liquidity Flowers, found near all kinds of shores

name: clothes_colonist_green
description: Light clothing, good for fast travel. Its green color is obtained from the peels of Yield Fruits, which thrive during the summer

name: clothes_colonist_red
description: Light clothing, good for fast travel. Its red color is obtained from the leaves of Copium plants, commonly found on the Bearish Mountains

name: clothes_colonist_white
description: Light clothing, good for fast travel. The white color is reserved for explorers who have proven themselves in the Degen Trials

name: clothes_colonist_yellow
description: Light clothing, good for fast travel. Its yellow color is obtained from the golden sands of the deserts of Etcal

name: clothes_garmet_blue

name: clothes_garmet_red

name: clothes_garmet_yellow
description: Traditional ritualistic attire whose yellow color symbolizes the sharing of wisdom

name: Deep Sleep Vitality Suit_dark

name: Deep Sleep Vitality Suit_draconic
description: Wearing this draconic suit makes you feel especially obedient. You also feel unaffected by heat

name: Deep Sleep Vitality Suit_golden
description: Wearing this golden suit makes you feel especially obedient. You’ll go to any lengths to follow orders

name: leather_dark

name: leather_draconic
description: This tight-fitting outfit is reserved for night-time missions, as sunlight tends to damage leather

name: leather_golden

name: partisan_red

name: robes_yellow
